  Key findings:
  • All individual alternatives (LR, XGB, LGB, CatBoost, RF, SVM) FAIL to beat baseline
  • Stacking (LR + CatBoost + RF) is the only architecture that beats it (+0.10pp)
  • Glicko-2 domain features alone do NOT improve on standard Elo (Exp1B: -0.31pp)
  • LR (and SVM) both closely match the blended baseline — XGBoost is the drag
  • Reducing to Top60 SHAP features loses <0.5pp with LR; XGBoost degrades sharply
  • EXP6 result: G2-domain + Stacking = 72.0833%  (-0.4167pp vs baseline)
  • EXP6 does NOT beat baseline — Elo + stacking (Exp5) remains the best result
